				\begin{document}$${\text{O}}_{2}^{ - }$$\end{document} ions. An energy band diagram that explains the sensing mechanism in the air and in NO2 ambient is shown in Fig. 21. Once the sensor is exposed into NO2 ambient, the NO2 molecules capture electrons from the sensing layer and adsorbed O2-\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
